article.headline: UC Davis 82, UC Riverside 52
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Joe Harden scored 22 points to lead four UC Davis players in double digits as part of an 82-52 victory over UC Riverside on Thursday night. The Aggies (7-12, 2-5 Big West) shot 51 percent from the field and snapped a five-game losing streak. They pulled ahead early and led by as many as 35 points in the second half. Mark Payne and Ryan Sypkens added 16 points each for the Aggies while Ryan Howley scored 10. The Highlanders (7-11, 2-4) took a 37-34 rebounding advantage but shot just 31.7 percent from the field. Javon Borum scored 12 points and was the only UC Riverside player in double digits.
